tv.amwa.maj.record

Interface VersionType

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<VersionType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VersionTypeImpl

    public interface VersionType
extends Comparable<VersionType>

    Specifies a 2-byte version number, consisting of a major and minor component.

    To make values of this type, use the following methods from the MAJ forge:

    • From its component parts: Forge.makeVersion(byte, byte);
    • A zero value: Forge.zeroVersion();
    • From a string representation as generated by toString(): Forge.parseVersion(String).
    See Also:
    TypeDefinitions.VersionType, ProductVersion

      • toString

        String toString()

        Formats the version number as a string representation. This format is:

        <major>.<minor>

        Note that "2.10" is a later version than "2.9".

        To convert the representation created by this method back into a version type value, use Forge.parseVersion(String).

        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        See Also:
        Forge.parseVersion(String)
